You know what you sell?

283
00:16:41,817 --> 00:16:43,918
Crap!

284
00:16:43,919 --> 00:16:46,921
Granny's Big Fudge Nuggets?
Maple Loops?

285
00:16:46,922 --> 00:16:51,259
Hey, Maple Loops is part of a nutritious,
balanced breakfast.

286
00:16:51,260 --> 00:16:55,163
Yeah, if you eat it with a steak
and some broccoli.

287
00:16:55,164 --> 00:16:58,600
And let me tell you another thing.
You had a shot at a real career.

288
00:16:58,601 --> 00:17:00,335
You could've played in great bands.

289
00:17:00,336 --> 00:17:02,604
You could've been a respected
studio musician.

290
00:17:02,605 --> 00:17:04,506
Don't you think I wanted that?

291
00:17:04,507 --> 00:17:07,097
I tried, Alan, and I failed.

292
00:17:07,276 --> 00:17:10,778
The truth is, if I hadn't started
writing jingles, I'd be playing

293
00:17:10,779 --> 00:17:15,179
